To quantify whether individual T cells switched between different speed states, i.e., whether over time similar speeds clustered together, we calculated for each individual track an autocorrelation function for speeds. Briefly, we computed the speed of each frame-to-frame velocity vector v. For each single track, we then collected all speed pairs sp that are separated by defined time intervals t. By computing the Spearman correlation coefficient for all n speed pairs sp of time intervals t with the MatLab function corr, we obtained a speed autocorrelation function for each track:1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
